Word Order: ...OVS

Noun Phrase: R X A... N FL... FN...

Parts of Speech:
Role - role particle that marks how noun interacts with verb, 2 components
Number - number
Adjective - modifies type of noun only
Noun - a type of thing
Function - converts noun in some way
Filter - Adjective-like function that filters out desired nouns

Verb Phrase: A... V D/OP... FN...

Parts of Speech:
Adjective - modifies type of verb
Verb - verb
Function - converts verb in some way
Describer/Option - describes verb(very small class)

Pronouns:
Gar/Dise
Dado/Dado
Nuu/Imo/Ifo
Garti/Diseti
Dadoti/Dadoti
Nuuti/Imoti/Ifoti
Notes
 - Dise means this self, becomes dis in modern
 - Gar -> ka
 - Dado -> Dad(dat) -> Da/Ta
 - Nuu -> Dïu -> Dü
 - Imo/Ifo -> ym/yf

